node.text: I have been working on an NFT digital Sculpture that Erodes and Reforms over the course of a year. This work is linked to the seasons and will decay and regrow every year forever. The edition which is part of a series of Digital Sculptures I am making will be released on @niftygateway on May 22nd at 7pm ET.  This idea of a sculpture that would decay and reform occurred to me over a decade ago but I couldn’t figure out how to make it. Until now.

node.text: The BLUE CRYSTALIZED PIKACHU Limited Edition is sold out. BLUE CRYSTALIZED PIKACHU is a sculpture that has been reimagined as a monument of Kanto uncovered through the passage of time. Modeled after the most well-known Pokémon character of all time, this edition is made of light blue cast resin and aluminum oxide, and is cast from a hand sculpted Pikachu made in Arsham Studio. Each edition is 33cm in height and weighs 5.13kg. BLUE CRYSTALIZED PIKACHU comes in Arsham studio designed housing with die-cut foam, sealing label, and a pair of custom art handling gloves. This is an edition of 500 pieces, and each BLUE CRYSTALIZED PIKACHU includes a holographic label verifying its edition number and authenticity.

node.text:
On the occasion of My recent solo exhibition Turning Wrenches, @librarystreetcollective has produced a set of five offset prints releasing this Friday, August 13th at 12 pm EST through their sister gallery @LouisBuhl, a gallery and project space that balances its exhibition programming with accessibility, offering unique works alongside high-quality editions. Each set includes five different prints featuring imagery pulled from the billboards I created for this year’s iteration of Public Matter, titled Fictional Advertisements. 

A nod to the Detroit automotive industry and international car culture as a whole, the billboards included in the public installation present fictional vintage advertisements for my altered and eroded car artworks. These uncanny ads invite their viewers to purchase vehicles for their own journey into the past or the future—time travel machines that can be personally owned and managed. There is a discussion at hand about the juxtaposition of eroding human-produced objects, the tenacity of geological materials that aid in efforts toward time travel, and the overall significant role time plays in the conversation.

I have signed 250 of each which will be released as a set. Unsigned versions also available.

Link in bio for the release Tomorrow. 

DanielArsham #DanielArsham #LouisBuhl #LibraryStreetCollective

node.text: Swipe all the way to see the original drawing for this lamp. It was the final piece for this collection and the most simple. These works are all made from laminated plywood with an alteration in the angle of laminated surface which gives the extreme variance in the wood grain. They are drawn and sculpted analog and then are milled on a digital CNC machine. I chose to leave them mostly unfinished so the tool pass and even some burn marks from the bit are visible in the surface. Its a digital/analog balance that very much retains the feeling of the hand within it. It will be part of my exhibition at @friedman_benda in NYC next Month.

node.text: Gardening with the boys. Keen observes will notice that I have changed the gravel in the garden to a finer grain with a lighter color. It has taken me a few years of trial and error to find the right material. If anyone is planning one, the material is Crushed Oyster Shells.
